<br>
Conflicts with the Teir'Dal have been on the rise in recent times. They have been growing more bold and threaten all that is benevolent. It is disturbing that they poison themselves with their beliefs in Innoruuk, but even more disturbing is they have taken up the practice of spreading their beliefs beyond their dark city.<br>
<br>
I have seen Barbarians, Halflings, and Humans bow before them. It is sickening that the Teir'Dal can corrupt the minds of others, for no sane being would willingly become one of their slaves. I had an opportunity to speak briefly with a Barbarian while attempting to rescue her. She proclaimed her alliegence to a sect of Teir'Dal known as the Violent Harvest. She refused to leave and called the guards upon me. I made a hasty exit and escaped, after a lengthy chase. I cannot forget the look in her eyes. At first she was cold, as if she had no soul, however, when she called for the guards, her voice was enraged but her eyes were sad. Despite her proclamation I am not convinced that she is there by her own will.<br>
<br>
Most Teir'Dal will never walk in the light, but there are hope for some. A few have proven themselves to possess good intentions. I believe that it is the doctrinal and oppresive upbringing that clouds their minds. It may yet be possible to save many Teil'Dal before they are irrevocably commited to a life of anguish.<br>
<br>
On the 19th of January I intend to lead a band of faithful follows into the Nektulos Forest. We will make our way to a fallen tree where younger Teir'Dal hunt and preach to them the benefits of the light. We will offer our blessings and try to save as many as we can. Should we find amongst them those who are not Teir'dal, then we shall double our efforts to restore logic to their minds and hope to their hearts.<br>
<br>
Many of those we encounter will not listen and some may become angry, and even call for the guards. We will come in peace, but we must be prepared to face a potential conflict. It is vital that the bridge spanning the Nerrius river remains passable for us, in case we are forced to withdrawl from the forest. A group of volunteers will maintain watch over the bridge to ensure our safe passage.<br>
<br>
It is known that Solus embraces the light, and as such you are invited to partake in this righteous cause. I understand that there are many important events to undergo in Norrath, but your help in this matter would be appreciated. For it is our duty to save those who are confused and repressed; we must act on their behalf before they condemn themselves to their dark fate.<br>
<br>
I await your reply with eagerness. May you all enjoy Erollisi's embrace.<br>
<br>
Rohwin Amoure Ardour<br>
Regent of Cursus Honorum<br>
<br>
OOC: The Violent Harvest is invited and encouraged to attend this event. It is my hope that you will offer good debate and other roleplaying. However, I have no intention of starting a guildwar or dueling, this event was scheduled primarily to offer an opportunity to meet each other and have some fun. We shall be in Nektulos for most of the afternoon of Saturday, January 19th PST. Hope to see you there.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#8E236B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/udaiunusdarkenvalor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daiunus Darkenvalor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/14/02 10:55:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=195.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A spy (I'm sure you've got some) has acquired a letter..</span><hr size=1> One of Daiunus's disciples entered the room, short of breath, but with a look of ultimate satisfaction upon his young face.  <br>
&quot; Speak boy, why do you have that foolish grin upon your face?&quot; Daiunus looked to the young boy, wondering if this one had lost his mind, to enter the Thresher's warroom in such a fit.<br>
&quot; My Thresher, I bring you a letter that I think you may find interesting,&quot;  The boy answered, the smile slowly leaving his face, realizing the consequences if the Thresher was not amused.  Daiunus motioned to the boy to come closer, and snatching it from the young Tier'dal's hand, he began to peruse the letter quickly.<br>
&quot; Abatteur, you have done well, this news should be investigated.  Make sure that we have some of the Chosen at this little gathering that this Lightborne fool has decided to hold within our Forest... and... fetch me Payle.. I think I must have words with her on this....&quot;<br>
The boy quickly rushed out of the room to deliver the news to the messengers of the Harvest, so that all the Chosen may come to protect their forest.<br>
<br>
<br>
Daiunus Darkenvalor<br>
Thresher of the Harvest<br>
<br>
