&quot;I see your servant got that to you with all haste, as bid.  I would have brought it myself, only I thought it best for it to switch hands a bit, lest I was followed.  I dare not risk alerting Rohwin, as of yet.&quot;<br>
She smiled at Daiunus.<br>
&quot;I trust this pleases you...?&quot; <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/upayle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>payle</A> at: 1/15/02 2:22:35 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#8E236B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/upravdameer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pravdameer</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dread Harvester (R)</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/15/02 8:47:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=195.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A spy (I'm sure you've got some) has acquired a letter..</span><hr size=1> The Prophet walked the caverns of Neriak - reacquainting himself with the place he was to once again call home. He stopped suddenly and looked at seemingly empty air as if listening to something unheard by passersby.<br>
&quot;What's that you say, Atoxus? They wouldn't dare...I cannot believe you...No I would not call you a liar...yes yes, I understand.&quot;<br>
The young Prophet slowly takes on a decidedly sadistic smile and begins a soft laugh.<br>
&quot;Indeed - the fools think they can 'save' The Father's chosen from the path of his Harvest. They will soon learn the folly of their ways, and the Father permitting I look forward to showing just how flawed their logic will be. Their paltry beliefs will melt away in the bonfires of True Hatred. Indeed...&quot;<br>
Pravdameer now begins to raise his voice gathering looks and whispers from passersby as he continues to walk the caverns.<br>
&quot;I say to you the Father's time is close at hand - the time is coming when his Harvest shall sweep across the lands and prepare the path for his return to the lands of Norrath and his Chosen children shall follow into their rightful place as the true leaders of the lands...&quot;<br>
The young prophet continues to rant and rave in a fanatical frenzy as some passersby seem to move a little faster, while others stop and listen. Before too long, he has a crowd about him as he preaches of the Father's return. Yes, the young priest had returned from the Father's plane, and there was much work still to be done. He would be there, the Father permitting...he would be there with proverbial bells on.<br>
<br>
